#X text 60 97 For musical purposes \, you might usually want to set the delay time according to a metronome beat. Hence \, you need to convert from a BPM value to ms \, which is possible with [bpm] from ELSE. Not only that \, but the object also lets you set a beat length. By default it considers that the BPM corresponds to "1/4" (a quarter note) \, but you can set other relative values. For instance \, 1/16 means the time it takes for a sixteenth note with a 60 BPM., f 57;
